  "prompt": "What do they call it when you get beat on a big play and you act injured in football?",
  "response": "In football, when a player gets beat on a big play and then acts injured to draw attention away from their mistake, it\u2019s often referred to as \"flopping\" or \"embellishing an injury.\" This tactic is sometimes used to save face or to stop the clock, but it\u2019s generally frowned upon and can be seen as unsportsmanlike. Players who do this risk losing credibility with teammates, coaches, and fans. In some cases, officials may also recognize the behavior and penalize it if it\u2019s deemed to be an attempt to deceive or delay the game.",
